All 3 tests pass. Here's the summary:

**`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4.** Replace it by moving the assertion into the test body using `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest() { CallThatThrows(); }

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest() {
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => CallThatThrows());
}
```

For **async** methods, use `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>()`. If you had `AllowDerivedTypes = true`, use `Assert.Throws<T>()` instead (matches derived types too).

> **Tip:** The `MSTEST0006` analyzer could have flagged this while still on v3.
